{{Infobox musical artist |image = Ali Ahmadifar, Iranian Composer.jpg |image_size = |background = non_vocal_instrumentalist |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|07|12}} |origin = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]] |instrument = |genre = [[Contemporary classical music]] |occupation = [[Composer]] |years_active = 1996–present }}
'''Ali Ahmadifar''' ({{lang-fa|علی احمدی فر}}) is an Iranian composer, teacher<ref>{{cite web|title= Biography – Facts, Birthday|url=http://www.artguilan.ir/Default.aspx?page=7705&section=pfitem&mid=20367&id=54912|website=www.artguilan.ir|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref> and researcher.<ref>{{cite web|title=Articles|url=http://musicreport.ir/profile-en.htm|website=www.musicreport.ir|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref>
==Book== * Author of the book "Stylistics of [[Arvo Pärt]] music ([[Persian language|Persian]]:سبک شناسی موسیقی آروو پارت)", published 2007.<ref>{{cite web|title=Reviewing of book|url=http://artguilan.net/Default.aspx?page=11726&section=litem&id=105069|website=artguilan.net|accessdate=12 December 2015}}</ref>
==Works== * "Where are you, o thou fairy?"(An Iranian variation) was performed by [[MDR Leipzig Radio Symphony Orchestra]] in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|title=MDR Leipzig Radio Symphony Orchestra|url=http://www.kulturkurier.de/veranstaltung_73176.html|website=www.kulturkurier.de|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref> * one of his works was performed by valid flute soloist Reza Najfar in 2008, [[Rasht]]. * "Minimove" (An Iranian variation for flute and strings) was performed by Camerata symphony orchestra led by Keyvan Mirhadi in 2008, [[Rasht]]. * "Bâng – e Robâb" was performed by the Avram ensemble in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=avram ensemble program|url=http://www.avram-ensemble.de/programm_01.html|website=www.avram-ensemble.de|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=AVRAM Ensemble Concert|url=http://archive-de.com/de/a/abrahamkonzerte.de/2015-09-19_6638222_8/AVRAM_Ensemble_Klangbr%C3%BCcke_zwischen_den_Kulturen/|website=archive-de.com|accessdate=12 December 2015}}</ref> * Radio contemporary music program editor and writer in Iranian radio broadcast network culture, 1999-2000. * The founder and first conductor of [[Gilan]] sinfonietta orchestra and choir, performing concert at Vahdat Hall, September 2007.<ref>{{cite web|title=Founder and first leader of Gilan orchestra|url=http://www.honaronline.ir/Pages/Printable-News-32970.aspx|website=www.honaronline.ir|accessdate=12 December 2015}}</ref>
