{{Infobox journal | title = Biblical Theology Bulletin | cover = BTB vol 40 no 1.gif | editor = David Bossman | discipline = [[Biblical studies]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Biblical Theol. Bull. | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] on behalf of Biblical Theology Bulletin Inc. | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1973–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journalsProdDesc.nav?prodId=Journal201924 | link1 = http://btb.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://btb.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 1774838 | LCCN = 72626645 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0146-1079 | eISSN = 1945-7596 }} The '''''Biblical Theology Bulletin''''' is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes articles and book reviews in the fields of [[biblical studies]] and, to a lesser extent, [[theology]]. The journal was established in 1971 under the [[Editor-in-chief|editorship]] of Leopold Sabourin ([[Pontifical Biblical Institute]]).<ref>[http://www.shu.edu/news/article/137898 A Global Reach for the Biblical Theology Bulletin]. Seton Hall University. Retrieved 7 March 2011.</ref> According to [[Michael J. Gorman|Michael Gorman]], the journal is "devoted primarily to social-scientific perspectives."<ref>[[Michael J. Gorman|Gorman, Michael]]. ''Elements of Biblical Exegesis''. Hendrickson, 2009, p. 216</ref>
